<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>AI Lego Curriculum — 8th Grade Edition</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --bg: #fdfcfb; --text: #2d3436; --accent: #0984e3;
    --lego-blue: #74b9ff; --lego-red: #ff7675; --lego-green: #55efc4;
  }
  body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); margin: 0; }
  header { background: var(--accent); color: white; padding: 20px; text-align: center; }
  .tabs { display: flex; justify-content: center; background: #dfe6e9; padding: 10px; gap: 5px; }
  .tab { padding: 10px 15px; border: none; cursor: pointer; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: bold; transition: 0.3s; }
  .tab:hover { background: #b2bec3; }
  .tab.on { background: var(--accent); color: white; }
  #content { padding: 40px; max-width: 800px; margin: auto; }
  .panel { display: none; animation: slideIn 0.5s ease-out; }
  .panel.on { display: block; }
  @keyframes slideIn { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }
  .card { background: white; border: 3px solid #dfe6e9; border-radius: 15px; padding: 25px; margin-bottom: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
  .widget { background: #f1f2f6; border-radius: 10px; padding: 15px; margin-top: 15px; text-align: center; font-size: 14px; }
  .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 12px; background: #ffeaa7; margin-bottom: 10px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>🤖 How AI Thinks: The Lego-Brick Universe</h1>
  <p>Explore the layers that turn words into intelligence!</p>
</header>

<div class="tabs">
  <button class="tab on" onclick="show(0)">L0: Bricks</button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="show(1)">L1: Colors/Maps</button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="show(2)">L3: Spotlights</button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="show(3)">L7: Schooling</button>
  <button class="tab" onclick="show(4)">L10: Manners</button>
</div>

<div id="content">
  <!-- L0 -->
  <div class="panel on" id="p0">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="badge">Layer 0 — The Word Breaker</span>
      <h2>Everything starts as tiny bricks!</h2>
      <p>An LLM can't read a whole sentence at once. It has to smash words into "Tokens" (Lego bricks). A short word like <b>"Cat"</b> is one single brick. But a long, scary word like <b>"Neurotransmitter"</b> gets smashed into 4 or 5 tiny pieces!</p>
      <div class="widget">
        <strong>Interactive Widget:</strong> <br>
        <button onclick="alert('SMASH! \"Cat\" $\\rightarrow$ [1 Brick]')">Smash "Cat"</button>
        <button onclick="alert('CRACK! \"Neurotransmitter\" $\\rightarrow$ [4 Bricks]')">Smash "Neurotransmitter"</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- L1 -->
  <div class="panel" id="p1">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="badge">Layer 1 — The Color & Map</span>
      <h2>Bricks need flavor and a GPS!</h2>
      <p>If all bricks were just grey, the AI wouldn't know the difference between "Apple" and "Dog." We dip every brick in a special color (<b>Embedding</b>) so it has a "flavor." Then we add a sticker (<b>Positioning</b>) so the AI knows which brick comes first!</p>
      <div class="widget">
        <strong>Interactive Widget:</strong> <br>
        <button onclick="alert('Color added! \"Apple\" is now RED 🍎')">Color "Apple"</button>
        <button onclick="alert('GPS added! Brick #1 is at position [0]')">Map "Brick #1"</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- L3 -->
  <div class="panel" id="p2">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="badge">Layer 3 — The Spotlight</span>
      <h2>The Flashlight Trick!</h2>
      <p>When the AI reads a sentence, it uses "<b>Attention</b>." This is like having a flashlight. One brick can shine its light on another brick to say: "Hey, you are important to me!" This helps the AI connect ideas.</p>
      <div class="widget">
        <strong>Interactive Widget:</strong> <br>
        <button onclick="alert('Flashlight ON! \"The\" is looking at \"Cat\" 🔦')">Shine Light</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- L7 -->
  <div class="panel" id="p3">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="badge">Layer 7 — The Schooling</span>
      <h2>Reading the Library</h2>
      <p>To become smart, the AI has to read trillions of books (<b>Pretraining</b>). It's like a student reading every single Wikipedia page ever written so it knows everything about history, science, and code.</p>
      <div class="widget">
        <strong>Interactive Widget:</strong> <br>
        <progress id="study-bar" value="0" max="100"></progress><br>
        <button onclick="document.getElementById('study-bar').value += 10">Read 1,000 more books!</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- L10 -->
  <div class="panel" id="p4">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="badge">Layer 10 — The Manners</span>
      <h2>Learning to be a good Assistant</h2>
      <p>A "base" AI might just repeat what you say. But through <b>RLHF</b>, we teach it manners! We give it "Gold Stars" when it is helpful and "Red Marks" when it is rude or wrong.</p>
      <div class="widget">
        <strong>Interactive Widget:</strong> <br>
        <button onclick="alert('⭐ GOLD STAR! The AI was polite!')">Reward Polite Answer</button>
        <button onclick="alert('❌ RED MARK! The AI lied!')">Correct Rude Answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
function show(idx) {
  const panels = document.querySelectorAll('.panel');
  const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tab');
  panels.forEach((p, i) => p.classList.toggle('on', i === idx));
  tabs.forEach((t, i) => t.classList.toggle('on', i === idx));
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
